Program: In Our Time
Title: Literature
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b018xw60
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 5 Jan 2012
Melvyn Bragg investigates how the written word, a technology originally used for accountancy, gave rise to all of human literature. He charts the emergence of poetry and history writing in the ancient world, inspects an ancient Egyptian precursor to Hamlet, and discovers how Greek literary traditions reached this country in the Middle Ages.Producer: Thomas Morris. Show less